docs.abstract: After 10 hours of deliberation, a jury found that Derek Chauvin had murdered George Floyd. We were in Minneapolis for the verdict and the reaction.
docs.snippet: After 10 hours of deliberation, a jury found that Derek Chauvin had murdered George Floyd. We were in Minneapolis for the verdict and the reaction.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Tuesday, after three weeks of jury selection, another three weeks of testimony and 10 hours of deliberations, Derek Chauvin, a former Minneapolis police officer, was found guilty of murder in the death of George Floyd.

docs.lead_paragraph: There are many appalling narratives emerging from the trial of the former police officer Derek Chauvin in the killing of George Floyd.

docs.abstract: Paramedics who responded to the scene said they did not see any signs of life in George Floyd. “In lay terms, I thought he was dead,” one said.
docs.snippet: Paramedics who responded to the scene said they did not see any signs of life in George Floyd. “In lay terms, I thought he was dead,” one said.
docs.lead_paragraph: The trial of Derek Chauvin, the former police officer charged with killing George Floyd in Minneapolis, entered a new phase on Thursday with the testimony of paramedics who responded to the scene, making it the first time that jurors heard about Mr. Floyd’s medical condition in the immediate aftermath of the arrest.

headline.main: Takeaways from Day 4 of the Derek Chauvin trial.

docs.abstract: For many observers, the trial of Derek Chauvin, the former Minneapolis police officer charged in George Floyd’s death, has felt like the culmination of years of outrage and grief over police killings of Black people in America. Video of the arrest that led to Mr. Floyd’s death inspired demonstrations that touched every corner of the country last summer, with protesters demanding justice for Mr. Floyd.

Garland to reopen the Justice Department’s investigation into the shooting, which was closed in December after the department said it could not charge the officers.

headline.main: Mother of Tamir Rice, a 12-year-old killed by the police, asks D.O.J. to reopen its investigation.

docs.lead_paragraph: Students streamed out of schools across Minnesota on Monday afternoon to protest racial injustice, in a coordinated action that coincided with closing arguments in the murder trial of Derek Chauvin, the former police officer charged with killing George Floyd.

headline.main: Minnesota students walk out of schools in solidarity with the racial justice movement.

docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — Two days after the streets of Minneapolis were filled with people celebrating the conviction of a police officer for the murder of George Floyd, the city returned to a period of mourning on Thursday for another Black man killed by a police officer.

headline.main: At Daunte Wright Funeral, Minneapolis Mourns the ‘Prince of Brooklyn Center’
headline.print_headline: In Minneapolis, a Day to Mourn ‘the Prince of Brooklyn Center’

docs.abstract: A bipartisan effort to change policing practices collapsed last summer after George Floyd’s murder by a white officer. Can a “guilty” verdict and President Biden’s call for action resurrect it?
docs.snippet: A bipartisan effort to change policing practices collapsed last summer after George Floyd’s murder by a white officer. Can a “guilty” verdict and President Biden’s call for action resurrect it?
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A day after a white Minneapolis police officer was found guilty of murdering George Floyd, a Black man, lawmakers in both parties said they were cautiously optimistic that the verdict could provide new momentum in Congress to overcome the hurdles that have thwarted a far-reaching police overhaul.

headline.main: Buoyed by Floyd Verdict, Congress Eyes New Bid to Overhaul Policing
headline.print_headline: Congress, Buoyed by the Floyd Verdict,  Resurrects Its Bid to Overhaul Policing

docs.lead_paragraph: On Tuesday, Derek Chauvin, a former Minneapolis police officer, was found guilty of second-degree murder, third-degree murder and second-degree manslaughter in the death of George Floyd, whose killing last May drew millions into the streets for the largest racial justice protests in generations.

headline.main: What Students Are Saying About The Verdict in the Derek Chauvin Trial
